		<font size="2" face="Verdana">
		<font size="1" face="Verdana">posted 8/12/2003 2:24:05 AM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<a href="US_Show.asp?id=57756">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to See the Profile for Bakanar" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="mailto:xvimlar@yahoo.com" target="_new">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/email.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Email Bakanar" width="24" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=Bakanar">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Bakanar" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=60&FN=Bard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=2013822&TN=In+detail%2E%2E%2E&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=2014291&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">1.  Find a group of social mobs, meaning they will assist each other when attacked.</P><P>2. Gain proximity agro from the mobs you want in your swarm, running near them works for many, for others you might need to actually use a song on them, use something like dispel magic so you get very low agro, do not do any damage to any member of the swarm.</P><P>3.  Charm one mob, I use a hotkey for this, I tap 6 on my keyboard and it cast's charm.</P><P>3.  Target another member of the soon to be swarm, I do this by tapping the F8 key which targets the nearest non-aligned mob.</P><P>4. Tell your pet to attack the newly targeted mob, I do this with another hotkey, '8' on my keyboard, /pet attack, quite simple.</P><P>5.  Tap the Tab key to retarget your pet and watch as his health drops, his friends will, if you've done it right, stop and all beat the crap out of him.</P><P>6.  When your pet gets down to say 20% health, keep him targeted mind you... go invis, I use Selo's Song of Travel but if you have a right click invis that works great, Hiding works too but it's unrealiable since our Hide skill caps so low.</P><P>7.  Invis breaks the charm, so now you simply lead the swarm around dotting your former pet... it is very important to NOT dot any other mobs in the swarm, JUST your former pet.  Once he's dead, hit F to target your next pet, charm, /pet attack, rinse repeat.</P><P>When you first charm a mob and get the swarm on him, you often have a few seconds in which to loot the corpse of the last victim of the swarm.  If you're in an area that is condusive to do so, when you're in the chant/dotting portion of the cycle run a the swarm around and pick up new members to feed it.  The trick is always having enough mobs in the swarm to wear your pet down to 20% or fewer hp during the 1 minute that the charm lasts.</P><P>Another key point, and I know I said this earlier but it's worth repeating... do not do any damage to any other members of the swarm.  You should only be chanting damage on your former pet and you will chant him untill he's dead before selecting the next target for your charm.</P><P>If the swarm dies down, ie. you can't find mobs to feed into it, you'll eventually get down to 2 mobs.. charm one, make it fight the other, chant/dot to help your pet kill the mob quickly then chant your pet down as well... this little pause is often useful for recovering mana.  Right now, it takes me 2 minutes, or 20 ticks, to regain the 60 mana it costs to cast Bewitchign Bravura.  So 2 minutes to recover the mana spent on a charm that lasts 1 minute, that's not a bad ratio.  That means with proper timing and occasional use of chant techniques over charming, I can keep a swarm going for hours on end with no loss in mana.</P><P>For the mana recovery, if you're curious, I have an Earring of the Solstice and one level of Mental Clarity along with the normal mana regen per turn.  <br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
</tr>
